inotify	 inotify (inode notify) is a Linux kernel subsystem that monitors
		 events in filesystems and reports those events to applications in
		 real time.

inotify-hookable

iwatch   iWatch is a Perl wrap to inotify to monitor changes in specific
		 directories or files, sending alarm to the system administrator
		 (or other destination) in real time. 

clsync   Clsync recursively watches for source directory and executes external
		 program to sync the changes

entr	 run arbitrary commands when file changes

